TY  - JOUR
AU  - He, Jie (Jack)
AU  - Qian, Jun (Q. J.)
AU  - Strahan, Philip E.
T1  - Does the Market Understand Rating Shopping? Predicting MBS Losses with Initial Yields
PY  - 2016
Y1  - 2016/02/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhv067
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 29
IS  - 2
SP  - 457
EP  - 485
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We study rating shopping on the MBS market. Outside of AAA, losses are higher on single-rated tranches than on multi-rated ones, and yields predict future losses for single-rated tranches, but not for multi-rated ones. Conversely, ratings have less explanatory power for single-rated tranches. These results suggest that single-rated tranches have been “shopped,” whereby pessimistic ratings never reach the market. For AAA-rated MBS, by contrast, 93% receive two or three such ratings, and those ratings agree 97% of the time. This ratings convergence suggests that agencies “cater” to investors, who cannot purchase a tranche unless it has multiple AAA ratings.Received January 22, 2014; accepted October 21, 2015 by Editor Andrew Karolyi.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhv067
ER  - 



