TY  - JOUR
AU  - Farre-Mensa, Joan
AU  - Ljungqvist, Alexander
T1  - Do Measures of Financial Constraints Measure Financial Constraints?
PY  - 2016
Y1  - 2016/02/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhv052
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 29
IS  - 2
SP  - 271
EP  - 308
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - Financial constraints are fundamental to empirical research in finance and economics. We propose two tests to evaluate how well measures of financial constraints actually capture constraints. We find that firms typically classified as constrained do not actually behave as if they were constrained: they have no trouble raising debt when their demand for debt increases exogenously and use the proceeds of equity issues to increase payouts to shareholders. Our evidence suggests that extant findings that have been attributed to constraints may instead reflect differences in the growth and financing policies of firms at different stages of their life cycles.Received December 9, 2014; accepted August 18, 2015 by Editor David Denis.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhv052
ER  - 



